This paper proposes a fair clustering method that is inspired by the popular K-Means clustering formulation. The paper focuses on the task of fair clustering for scenarios involving multiple multi-valued or numeric sensitive attributes. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with clustering and fairness. The paper also involves computational fairness, which falls under the sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with privacy and security, which falls under the sub-category cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper involves the use of algorithms and data structures, which falls under the sub-category cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper involves social and information networks, which falls under the sub-category cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
